revision.text:
{{Infobox games | Name = 1985 Pacific Mini Games | Logo = 1985_South_Pacific_Mini_Games_logo.png | Size = 168px | Optional caption = | Host city = [[Rarotonga]] | Country = [[Cook Islands]] | Motto = | Nations participating = 16 | Athletes participating = ~700<ref name = pim-sep-85-p25/> | Events = 6 sports | Opening ceremony = {{Start date|1985|07|31}} | Closing ceremony = {{End date|1985|08|09}} | Officially opened by = | Athlete's Oath = | Judge's Oath = | Torch Lighter = | Stadium = | previous = [[1981 South Pacific Mini Games|1981 Honiara]] | next = [[1989 South Pacific Mini Games|1989 Nuku'alofa]] }} The '''1985 South Pacific Mini Games''' were held at [[Rarotonga]] in the [[Cook Islands]] from 31 July to 9 August 1985. It was the second edition of the [[South Pacific Mini Games]].<ref name = 1985-mini-games/>
The new stadium built for the games had a grass track but several South Pacific Games athletics records were broken at the 1985 games including the women's 800 metres.<ref name = 1985-mini-games/> The track and field competition also served as a selection trial for the Oceania team to compete at the [[1985 IAAF World Cup|IAAF World Cup]] in [[Canberra]].<ref name = ct-6-8-85/>
==Participating countries== Sixteen Pacific nations participated in the Games:<ref name = 1985-mini-games/>
{{columns-list|colwidth=17em| * {{flag|American Samoa}} * {{flag|Cook Islands}} * {{flag|Fiji|1970}} * {{flag|French Polynesia|1946}}, "Tahiti" <!--* {{flag|Guam}} --> * {{flag|Kiribati}} * {{flag|Marshall Islands}} * {{flag|Nauru}} * {{flag|New Caledonia|1853}} * {{flag|Niue}} * {{flag|Norfolk Island}} <!--* {{flag|Northern Marianas}} --> <!--* {{flag|Palau}} --> * {{flag|Papua New Guinea}} * {{flag|Solomon Islands}} <!--* {{flag|Tokelau}}--> * {{flag|Tonga}} <!--* {{flag|Tuvalu}}--> <!--* {{flag|Micronesia}}--> * {{flag|Vanuatu}} * {{flag|Wallis and Futuna}} * {{flag|Western Samoa|name=Western Samoa}} }}
