'''Dr. Panda''' (formerly '''TribePlay''')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adweek.com/socialtimes/tribeplay-rebrands-as-dr-panda-in-honor-of-childrens-game-franchise/617061|title=TribePlay Rebrands as Dr. Panda in Honor of Children's Game Franchise|work=adweek.com}}</ref> is an independent [[China|Chinese]] kids
[[video game developer]] focused on creating educational applications for kids on [[smartphone]]s and [[Tablet computer|tablets]], and based in [[Chengdu]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://venturebeat.com/2015/03/17/dr-panda-passes-40-million-installs-showing-that-kids-in-china-and-the-west-play-the-same-way/|title=Dr. Panda passes 40 million installs, showing that kids in China and the West play the same way|work=Venture Beat}}</ref> The company's series of Dr. Panda games includes more than 25 apps that focus on role-playing experiences that are accessible to young kids,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://thenextweb.com/asia/2012/12/04/china-based-tribeplay-raises-750000-to-produce-monthly-dr-panda-kids-games/|title=China-based TribePlay raises $750,000 to produce monthly Dr. Panda kids’ games|work=thenextweb.com}}</ref> such as grocery shopping, cooking and airline travel. The games are available on platforms including [[iOS]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]] and [[Windows Phone]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.drpandagames.com/|title=TribePlay - Games|accessdate=2016-09-04}}</ref> The applications have been installed over 50 million times worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bestappsforkids.org/health/dr-panda-bathtime/|title=Dr. Panda Bath Time|work=Best Apps for Kids}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://us.blastingnews.com/lifestyle/2016/09/dr-panda-releases-dr-panda-bath-time-on-september-8-2016-001106701.html|title=Dr. Panda releases ‘Dr. Panda Bath Time’ on September 8, 2016|work=Blasting News}}</ref> In 2015, [[Apple Inc.]] named ''Dr. Panda's Restaurant 2'' as its "Free App of the Week".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bidnessetc.com/34914-apple-inc-free-app-of-the-week-childrens-game-dr-pandas-restaurant-2/|title=Apple Inc. Free App Of The Week: Children's Game "Dr. Panda's Restaurant 2"|work= BisnessEtc.}}</ref> and again, with ''Dr. Panda Ice Cream Truck'' in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.phonearena.com/news/Dr.-Pandas-Ice-Cream-Truck-is-this-weeks-free-App-Store-game_id84124|title=Dr. Panda's Ice Cream Truck is this week's free App Store game|work= Phone Arena}}</ref>

== History ==

=== 2011-2012: Beginnings and mainstream success. ===
Dr. Panda (previously TribePlay) was founded in 2011 by Thijs Bosma<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adweek.com/socialtimes/tribeplay-rebrands-as-dr-panda-in-honor-of-childrens-game-franchise/617061|title=TribePlay Rebrands as Dr. Panda in Honor of Children;s Game Franchise|work=Social Times}}</ref> and began development for the future Dr. Panda franchise in early 2012.<ref>http://drpanda.com/word-thijs-bosma-drpanda-founder-ceo/</ref> By March 2012, Dr. Panda launched their first game, ''Dr. Panda Teach Me!'' on the App Store.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-A0pFzwu990|title=Dr.Panda Teach Me! Trailer |work=YouTube}}</ref> Since then the company has released 29 more titles that have surpassed 50 million downloads in over 100 countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bestappsforkids.org/health/dr-panda-bathtime/|title=Dr. Panda Bath Time|work=Best Apps for Kids}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://us.blastingnews.com/lifestyle/2016/09/dr-panda-releases-dr-panda-bath-time-on-september-8-2016-001106701.html|title=Dr. Panda releases ‘Dr. Panda Bath Time’ on September 8, 2016|work=Blasting News}}</ref> making them the third largest developer of paid kids apps worldwide on iOS—and largest independent developer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/pressreleases/238917/TribePlay_Changes_Name_to_Dr_Panda_as_its_ChildrenrsquosEducational_Games_Surpass_40_Million_Installs.php|title=TribePlay Changes Name to Dr. Panda as its Children's Educational Games Surpass 40 Million Installs|work=Gamasutra}}</ref>

=== 2013-Present: Rebranding and expansion. ===
Dr. Panda expanded into 3D graphics with the release of ''Dr. Panda Home'' in 2013. It was featured as one of ''[[The Guardian]]'''s Best 20 Android Apps of the Week in 2013<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2013/nov/29/best-android-apps-virgin-tv-ridiculous-fishing|title=20 best Android apps and games this week|work=The Guardian}}</ref> and was awarded with an "Editor's Choice Award" by ''Children's Technology Review''.<ref>http://reviews.childrenstech.com/ctr/review.php?id=17358</ref>

In 2015, TribePlay rebranded to Dr. Panda to better reflect the personality and popularity of the game franchise.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adweek.com/socialtimes/tribeplay-rebrands-as-dr-panda-in-honor-of-childrens-game-franchise/617061|title=TribePlay Rebrands as Dr. Panda in Honor of Children;s Game Franchise|work=Social Times}}</ref>

In early 2016, the company launched the ''Dr. Panda Plush Toy'' along with official ''Dr. Panda T-shirts'' that are available to buy from the US Amazon store.<ref>http://drpanda.com/dr-panda-plush-toy/</ref><ref>https://www.amazon.com/Dr-Panda-Plush-Toy/dp/B010SIECE8/</ref><ref>https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B01B12QBBC/ref=s9_dcacsd_bhz_bw_c_x_2</ref>

== Popular games ==
According to the company's official [http://www.drpanda.com website], Dr. Panda games combines role play, open-ended play and expressive characters.<ref>https://venturebeat.com/2015/03/17/dr-panda-passes-40-million-installs-showing-that-kids-in-china-and-the-west-play-the-same-way/</ref> Each game explores a different aspect of everyday life from cooking and traffic, to gardening and art.<ref>https://thenextweb.com/asia/2012/12/04/china-based-tribeplay-raises-750000-to-produce-monthly-dr-panda-kids-games/</ref>

=== Dr. Panda's Restaurant 2 ===
''Dr. Panda's Restaurant 2'' is an interactive cooking-based game for children aged 6–8. It follows the main character Dr. Panda as he tries to run his beach-side restaurant as efficiently as possible, satisfying various customers that visit during the day. The customers in the game are animals ranging from hippos and elephants to polar bears, and each customer orders a dish of their liking when they arrive.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bidnessetc.com/34914-apple-inc-free-app-of-the-week-childrens-game-dr-pandas-restaurant-2/|title=Apple Inc. Free App Of The Week: Children's Game "Dr. Panda's Restaurant 2"|work= BisnessEtc.}}</ref> The game aims to educate children on the concept of preparing food, and familiarizes them with basic ingredients and the steps involved in preparing dishes like pastas and pizzas.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bidnessetc.com/34914-apple-inc-free-app-of-the-week-childrens-game-dr-pandas-restaurant-2/|title=Apple Inc. Free App Of The Week: Children's Game "Dr. Panda's Restaurant 2"|work= BisnessEtc.}}</ref>

=== Hoopa City ===
''Hoopa City'', developed by Dr. Panda, is a city-building game for children aged 5–8.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jconline.com/story/tech/2014/08/03/kids-tech-lego-apps/13462299/|title=Two terrific town-building apps for LEGO lovers|work=JConline}}</ref> The user joins the character, Hoopa, a construction-loving hippo who teaches the player to build on a scrollable meadow-like, gridded globe. At the top of the screen is a choice of seven building elements, including brick, water, electricity, roads, nature, money and a heart. To discover the more than 70 buildings, kids will need to combine the elements in different ways.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/columnist/gudmundsen/2014/08/02/apps-lego-lovers/13364029/|title=Two terrific town-building apps for LEGO lovers|work=USA Today}}</ref>

Hoopa City has been compared to [[SimCity]], but for preschoolers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://topbestappsforkids.com/hoopa-city-app-review-12264/|title=Creating your own City with the brand new Dr. Panda game for kids|work=Top Best Apps for Kids}}</ref><ref>http://childrenstech.com/blog/archives/15063</ref> Hoopa City has been awarded the "Honors Award" at the 2014 ''National Parenting Publications Awards''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nappaawards.com/single-post/2014/10/15/Hoopa-City-by-TribePlay-Limited|title=Hoopa City by TribePlay Limited|work=National Parenting Product Awards}}</ref> ''Tech with Kids'' named Hoopa City as their "Best Pick App" in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/columnist/gudmundsen/2014/12/06/10-top-kids-apps-of-2014/19809969/|title=10 top kids apps of 2014|work= USA Today}}</ref> It was also featured in "10 top kids apps of 2014" by ''USA Today''.

== Honors and awards ==
Dr. Panda regularly tops the store charts, and has ranked as the #1 kids game in the App Store in over 50 countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kidscreen.com/2015/05/07/dr-panda-on-designing-apps-with-cross-border-appeal/|title=Dr. Panda on designing apps with cross-border appeal|work=Kidscreen}}</ref> As of 2016, Dr. Panda has gone on to win awards from ''National Parenting Publications (NAPPA)'', ''Children's Technology Review'' and ''Parent's Choice''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nappaawards.com/single-post/2014/10/15/Dr-Pandas-Restaurant-2-by-TribePlay-Limited|title=Dr. Panda's Restaurant 2 by TribePlay Limited|work=National Parenting Product Awards}}</ref><ref>http://www.nappaawards.com/single-post/2014/10/15/Hoopa-City-by-TribePlay-Limited</ref><ref>http://reviews.childrenstech.com/ctr/review.php?id=16702</ref>
<ref>http://reviews.childrenstech.com/ctr/review.php?id=17358
</ref><ref>http://www.parents-choice.org/product.cfm?product_id=31242&StepNum=1&award=aw</ref><ref>http://www.parents-choice.org/product.cfm?product_id=32420&StepNum=1&award=aw
</ref><ref>http://www.parents-choice.org/product.cfm?product_id=33566&StepNum=1&award=aw
</ref>

In 2015, Dr. Panda was featured as the Developer of the Month (October) by ''Good App Guide''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fundamentallychildren.com/good-app-guide/apps-by-brand/good-apps-by-dr-panda/|title=Good Apps by Dr. Panda|work=Fundamentally Children}}</ref> In the 2016 ''Loved by Parents Awards'', ''Dr. Panda in Space'' was nominated and awarded the Platinum Award for "Best Family App" and Gold for "Best Children's App".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lovedbyparents.com/lovedbyparents-award-winners-2016/|title=Lovedbyparents Award Winners 2016|work=Loved by Parents}}</ref>

