An '''eye popper''' or '''rubber popper''' is a popular children's toy.
==Information== An eye popper is a small, [[dome]]-shaped piece of [[rubber]] or similar material resembling a half of a rubber ball; the shape of a smile is often imprinted on the dome. When pressed, the toy inverts, but after a few seconds, it pops back into its original shape, making a loud popping sound. If resting on the ground when this happens, the toy [[Deflection (physics)|will fly]] several feet into the air. The eye popper's behavior resembles the process by which a ball compresses upon hitting a hard surface.<ref name="Hopper Popper">{{cite journal|last=Katz|first=David|title=Hopper Popper|year=2005|pages=1–2}}</ref>
