==Reception==
{{video game reviews
|MC=(PC) 83/100<ref name="MCPC">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/hitman-2|title=Hitman 2 for PC Reviews - Metacritic|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=November 14, 2018}}</ref><br>(PS4) 82/100<ref name="MCPS4">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/hitman-2|title=Hitman 2 for PlayStation 4 Reviews - Metacritic|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=November 14, 2018}}</ref><br>(XONE) 84/100<ref name="MCONE">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/hitman-2|title=Hitman 2 for Xbox One Reviews - Metacritic|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=November 14, 2018}}</ref>
}}
''Hitman 2'' received "generally favorable" reviews, according to [[review aggregator]] [[Metacritic]].{{r|MCPS4|MCONE|MCPC}}

[[Gamespot]] gave the game a positive review writing, “Hitman 2 is a familiar experience, but in the Hitman world, familiarity is an incredible strength“.<ref>https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/hitman-2-review-okay-you-can-stop-hitting-me-now/1900-6417031/</ref> [[The Verge]] also praised the game writing, “Hitman 2 is the most refined and rewarding game in the series” noting it was a flawless execution.<ref>https://www.theverge.com/2018/11/13/18089674/hitman-2-review-ps4-xbox-pc</ref>

Trusted Reviews rated the game 9/10, writing, “Hitman 2 is an iterative rework of the formula set up by 2016’s bold Hitman reboot. It’s the best Hitman game so far, and I’d absolutely recommend it wholeheartedly”.<ref>https://www.trustedreviews.com/reviews/hitman-2</ref> [[The Guardian]] gave the game 4/5 stars, writing, “Assassination missions that reward subterfuge – such as wearing a giant flamingo suit or loosening a racing driver’s wheel – make this a surprisingly creative sequel”.<ref>https://www.theguardian.com/games/2018/nov/13/hitman-2-review-playstation-4-xbox-one-pc-io-interactive</ref> [[Screen Rant]] also spoke highly positive of the game, giving it 4/5 stars, adding that the game is an Impressive Assassination Simulation.<ref>https://screenrant.com/hitman-2-review/</ref> [[Geek.com]] also spoke positive of the game, writing, “Hitman 2 is the New Gold Standard for Stealth Games”.<ref>https://www.geek.com/games/hitman-2-is-the-new-gold-standard-for-stealth-games-1761235/</ref>

===Sales===

''Hitman 2'' debuted at tenth place in the UK's all-format sales charts, selling 90% fewer copies than ''[[Hitman: Absolution]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Phillips |first1=Tom |title=Spyro sold more physical copies at launch than Fallout 76 |url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-11-19-spyro-sold-more-physical-copies-at-launch-than-fallout-76 |website=Eurogamer |publisher=Gamer Network |accessdate=19 November 2018}}</ref> It released in a competitive week that also saw the launch of new releases including ''[[Pokémon: Let's Go]]'', ''[[Spyro Reignited Trilogy]]'' and ''[[Fallout 76]]''.<ref name="gamesindustry">{{cite news |title=Pokémon and Spyro top hyper competitive week at UK games retail |url=https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2018-11-18-pok-mon-and-spyro-top-hyper-competitive-week-at-uk-games-retail |work=[[GamesIndustry.biz]] |date=November 18, 2018}}</ref>

